<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="326" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.15/1651.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Russell</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-26T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department trusts situation foreshadowed in your November 20, 5 p.m. will
                            not materialize. The resignation of President Jiménes would be a matter
                            of regret and concern. The Department will be glad if you will so inform
                            him and assure him of our support in any efforts that he may undertake
                            with a view to secure peace and prosperity in Santo Domingo.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>